The Security Council notes with concern the postponement of the first round of the presidential elections, scheduled to take place on November 29, 2009, according to the statement dated May 18, 2009 of the Permanent Consultative Framework established by the Political Agreement of Ouagadougou, had been approved by all the main political actors in Côte d'Ivoire.	1
9. The Al-Haramain Foundation (United States of America), a listed entity, (QE.A.117.04) has filed a new lawsuit against the Government in the Federal District Court of Oregon, in addition to a previously filed lawsuit that remains pending in the United States. Al-Haramain claims that the United States' decision to impose sanctions against him was arbitrary, was not supported by substantial evidence, and violated his right to due process (as it did not explain the factual basis of the Government's action and used evidence confidential information not submitted to the organization), their right to be free from improper searches and seizures (based on the freezing of their assets) and their rights to freedom of expression, association and religion. Al-Haramain also claims that the Government's refusal to allow him to use frozen assets to pay his lawyers constituted a violation of his right to due process.	1
